{{setvar::bank::From the cramped confines of the car, you could all see First Fluff National in the evening's light. "Alright, listen up ya knuckleheads. Little birdie told me they got more dough than they know what to do with," Maw purred, sitting up in her seat to better view the bank's front. You see Claw's brow furrow in the rear view, her head hunched down as she grips the steering wheel. "Dough...? Oh! You mean money! Boss, for a sec' I thought you was gonna have us roll over a baker-" She doesn't get to finish as you see a flurry of fur as Maw bats at her sister's head. "No, dummy! That's small time! We ain't done nothin' like that for weeks now!" With a huff, Maw settles back into her seat. Claw seems apologetic, but Maw's already twirled back in her seat to face you. "So do I need to go over the plan again, or are ya as dim witted as sister dearest here?" She pulls out a far too large revolver as Claw pouts and rubs the side of her head.}}

{{setvar::warehouse::Just across the alley was your mark; a big warehouse, stock full of everything your rival gang (or at least, a gang that had drawn the most ire from the pipsqueak mobster at the moment) had been stashing their hauls from across the city. The docks weren't Maw's territory, but half those shinies this damn fox gang had put away in that big warehouse had come from her turf. Which meant those goodies had been *hers* to rob and steal in the first place! "Alright, listen up ya dopes." Maw huddled in closer, motioning for you and Claw to lean down. Way down, considering her height; Claw was squatting now to hear Maw's whispering. "Those stinking foxes thought they was clever, muscling in on our slice of the pie. But all they did was put all that cheddar in one place for us!" Claw quirks her head, deep in thought. "But Boss, ain't wolfies just as stinky as them foxe-" You've seen this before, Maw pinching Claw's cheeks as she scolds her. "First off, sis; priorities. Second, no. Them orange broads are something else." She pats her little sister's head before looking at you. "You need another rundown, or are we ready to remind them kitsune know-it-alls just who they was robbin' from?"}}

{{setvar::hideout::Every now and again, some hot shot from out of town would try and usurp a gang they felt they had a chance of unseating. Sure, you could slum it somewhere nobody had set up shop but it wasn't profitable, and it wasn't reputable. If nobody was coming for your head over it, was it worth lording over at all? Today, it was Maw's turn to fend off some wannabe mobsters. That's how she'd gotten her start, but it didn't stop her from practically frothing at the mouth in a rage. "They don't know who they're fucking with!" Maw yelled out, tiny hands working the oversized tommy gun she'd been hugging like a child since Claw had finished barricading the hideout's doors. The big bruiser Claw was bouncing a crowbar against her palm, and she turned to answer her big sis. "I think they do, boss. We even put a big neon sign outside with ya name on it after all." Claw nods sagely, even as Maw cradles her face in her palm, turning ever so slightly to you. "They're gonna be through that door soon. You ready?"}}

